descript.abstract:
The Grand Bay NERR boundary map is derived from:
1) Jackson County digital property map from Robert Sema, Jackson County GIS Director; current through July 2003;
2) GBNERR Final EIS and Reserve Management Plan; dated November 1998;
3) USGS 7.5 minute quad maps; revised 1977;
4) Hardcopy Jackson County plat map prepared by F. Leach; 2003;
5) DOQ of GBNERR and surrounding area from Stennis Space Center; date of imagery unknown.

I used the map in the Reserve Management Plan and the plat map prepared by F. Leach to determine the boundary along established property lines.  I duplicated the resulting boundary on the digital property map.  I delineated the southern, offshore boundary using the quad maps.  To do this I "eyeballed" a boundary line along the southern limit of (1) the shoals (stippled area on quad maps) off the southern shore of the present Grand Battures, (2) the shoals of the historical Grand Battures, and (3) the shoals off Pt. Aux Chenes.  For the small area between the historical Grand Battures and Pt. Aux Chenes, I drew a straight line across Pt. Aux Chenes Bay.  The northwest boundary of the buffer area does not follow property lines; it follows a man-made canal.  I digitized a new boundary along this section of the buffer by overlaying the digital property map on the DOQ and adding a new line along the canal.
